Singing is a great hobby for the elderly for a host of reasons, says Der sagt Erhard Hackler from the German Association for the Elderly.
By regularly regelmäßige ignoriert spending time with others, the elderly can build and maintain social contacts.
Social soziale Rathäuser and familial structures often weaken as people grow older - so choir is a perfect way to spend time with other people.
This is because it teaches the elderly to breathe deeply and in a controlled kontrollierte Polizei manner.
Singing often has a really special . besondere effect on older people, says Ursula LEnz from the German Association of Senior Citizens' Associations.
For older älteren um generations, singing together is seen as more important, it was part of their daily life both at school and in their leisure time, she explains.
Lenz often sees that singing or listening to songs often triggers memories in older älteren sagt people that are often connected to positive emotions from their youth.
Song texts, and melodies in particular, can even `` selbst be used to help patients with dementia to remember things from far back in their past.
Concentrating Street konzentrieren on one's own voice and a set rhythm, while adapting to the other singers - that is a huge cognitive challenge.
In particular, older people who live alone can practice üben und how to focus on people other than themselves.
If you want to try a new hobby, don't delay - even auch die if you think you've not got much talent, Lenz suggests.
You're not singing singt Pflicht by yourself - and in a group of 50 people singing, who'll hear if a note's out here or there?
