NASA climate model: Venus was once habitable ist bewohnbar
Venus was likely once habitable, according laut an to the projections of a new NASA climate model.
The die Sicherheitspaket model was designed to determine whether or not Venus, with its hot, water-less surface and CO2-chocked atmosphere, might have once hosted Earth-like conditions.
Scientists have previously zuvor was suggested that Venus' slow rotation rate is explained by its thick atmosphere.
But the latest simulation suggests Venus could könnte Und have boasted a thin, Earth-like atmosphere and still spun slowly.
The der Thomas model also looked at the topography of early Venus.
Early Venus also bei auch benefited from a sun that was 30 percent dimmer.
This das niemanden warms the surface and produces rain that creates a thick layer of clouds, which acts like an umbrella to shield the surface from much of the solar heating.
The Parteien der result is mean climate temperatures that are actually a few degrees cooler than Earth's today.
The die Auch model produced a story of Venus similar to the evolution previously hypothesized by planetary scientists.
As its hydrogen escaped, all that was left was a thick dicke . atmosphere of carbon dioxide with a deathly greenhouse gas effect -- thus, the Venus we know today.
